1
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:51,156 --> 00:00:54,660
Only a taste of something vile
will straighten them out.

3
00:00:55,619 --> 00:00:57,579
I will make them cry their eyes out.

4
00:01:14,971 --> 00:01:17,683
Your Highness, I have brought your tonic.

5
00:01:17,766 --> 00:01:20,268
I shall forgo it. I am fatigued.

6
00:01:20,352 --> 00:01:21,561
SUPPLEMENT TO THE GREAT LEARNING

7
00:01:29,194 --> 00:01:31,863
SEONGHYEON PAVILION

8
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:05,981
Do not move.
Unless you have a life to spare.

9
00:03:16,468 --> 00:03:19,387
-How in the world…
-His accomplices must be nearby.

10
00:03:20,138 --> 00:03:21,598
Conduct a thorough search.

11
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:33,902
Search everywhere!

12
00:03:33,985 --> 00:03:35,570
Scour the area!

13
00:03:45,247 --> 00:03:47,082
Who goes there?

14
00:03:47,582 --> 00:03:50,710
And why would you just shoot
an arrow at me for no reason?

15
00:03:52,462 --> 00:03:53,713
And who are you?

16
00:03:53,797 --> 00:03:55,382
What are you doing here?

17
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:57,133
Please spare my life.

18
00:03:57,217 --> 00:03:58,927
So you admit you deserve to die.

19
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:01,054
Who sent you to spy on me?

20
00:04:01,137 --> 00:04:03,139
No one sent me.

21
00:04:04,015 --> 00:04:05,392
I came of my own accord.

22
00:04:05,475 --> 00:04:07,310
A mere palace maid like you?

23
00:04:07,394 --> 00:04:10,146
You prowled these palace grounds
of your own accord?

24
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:12,065
How dare you lie to me!

25
00:04:12,148 --> 00:04:13,650
It is the truth.

26
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:17,320
I just wanted to get back at my peers.

27
00:04:17,404 --> 00:04:18,780
"Get back at them"?

28
00:04:19,865 --> 00:04:21,283
Lift your head.

29
00:04:23,994 --> 00:04:27,622
I deserve death…
No, I mean, spare my life.

30
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,083
Please…

31
00:04:30,709 --> 00:04:31,918
I will not kill you.

32
00:04:32,002 --> 00:04:33,420
Lift your head.

33
00:04:39,134 --> 00:04:40,135
Wait.

34
00:04:46,516 --> 00:04:49,477
You are the palace maid
who was undergoing initiation rites.

35
00:05:02,991 --> 00:05:05,035
Thank you for your help back then.

36
00:05:05,118 --> 00:05:08,496
Not being able to offer you my thanks
has weighed on me ever since.

37
00:05:10,206 --> 00:05:13,209
May I ask for your name, my lord?

38
00:05:14,753 --> 00:05:17,088
That is not something
I can easily tell you.

39
00:05:18,715 --> 00:05:20,383
What is your name?

40
00:05:20,884 --> 00:05:24,304
Yes, my name is…

41
00:05:25,931 --> 00:05:27,098
Look out!

42
00:05:36,066 --> 00:05:37,400
Are you all right?

43
00:05:38,276 --> 00:05:39,361
Yes.

44
00:05:39,444 --> 00:05:41,196
I am fine.

45
00:05:42,072 --> 00:05:43,406
And you, my lord?

46
00:05:43,490 --> 00:05:44,407
After them!

47
00:05:44,491 --> 00:05:46,284
You should return to your quarters.

48
00:05:46,368 --> 00:05:48,328
More blades lie in wait in the dark.

49
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:54,626
Please

50
00:05:55,919 --> 00:05:57,504
be safe, my lord.

51
00:05:59,965 --> 00:06:04,219
EPISODE 3
A WHOLE NEW REALITY

52
00:06:04,302 --> 00:06:06,972
Here you are.
I've been looking everywhere for you.

53
00:06:07,722 --> 00:06:10,767
That face… He is no apparition.

54
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:11,768
What are you doing here?

55
00:06:15,021 --> 00:06:18,858
Degenerate. I am going to need you
to be my shield for a moment.

56
00:06:39,546 --> 00:06:40,797
Hey.

57
00:06:42,090 --> 00:06:43,466
What's wrong with you?

58
00:06:44,676 --> 00:06:46,636
Listen, this is a bit…

59
00:06:47,595 --> 00:06:49,431
There's been a misunderstanding.

60
00:06:49,514 --> 00:06:50,974
I…

61
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:55,270
This isn't what I was asking for.

62
00:06:55,854 --> 00:06:58,231
I was wondering where you rushed off to.

63
00:06:58,314 --> 00:06:59,190
Secret date?

64
00:06:59,274 --> 00:07:00,442
No, it's not like that.

65
00:07:00,525 --> 00:07:03,028
Hey, woman, will you get off me…

66
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,007
What the hell is going on here?

67
00:07:24,924 --> 00:07:27,260
I had something to tell you,
but I see you're busy.

68
00:07:27,343 --> 00:07:30,764
No, seriously, I don't know her like that.

69
00:07:30,847 --> 00:07:33,475
You don't even know her
and you're already so bold.

70
00:07:35,518 --> 00:07:36,811
All right, fine.

71
00:07:37,437 --> 00:07:38,313
Okay, I got you.

72
00:07:38,396 --> 00:07:40,815
You have your hands full.
I'll catch you later.

73
00:07:44,444 --> 00:07:46,029
Think of your social standing.

74
00:07:46,112 --> 00:07:48,239
Whatever the reason,
try not to do that in public.

75
00:07:48,323 --> 00:07:50,575
I told you it's not like that.

76
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:03,546
Is he gone?

77
00:08:06,716 --> 00:08:07,759
Jeez.

78
00:08:15,183 --> 00:08:17,018
Shin Seo-ri, have you lost your damn mind?

79
00:08:17,102 --> 00:08:20,897
I was in a difficult situation,
and you proved to be quite useful.

80
00:08:21,523 --> 00:08:22,565
Farewell.

81
00:08:23,983 --> 00:08:24,859
Where are you going?

82
00:08:24,943 --> 00:08:27,695
You scoundrel! Let go of me this instant!

83
00:08:27,779 --> 00:08:29,072
Come here.

84
00:08:29,155 --> 00:08:31,116
You made a complete fool out of me.

85
00:08:32,408 --> 00:08:33,535
What was that just now?

86
00:08:33,618 --> 00:08:35,245
You made me look like a complete pervert.

87
00:08:35,328 --> 00:08:36,371
What's your deal?

88
00:08:36,454 --> 00:08:37,956
That is rich,

89
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:41,459
coming from a degenerate who pulls
women into his arms in plain daylight.

90
00:08:41,543 --> 00:08:42,627
That was different.

91
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:44,629
It was because
you just ran into the street.

92
00:08:44,712 --> 00:08:45,922
It did not happen just once.

93
00:08:46,005 --> 00:08:48,299
You also grabbed me
when I sensed that assassin.

94
00:08:48,383 --> 00:08:51,052
I let it slide then,
given how dire things were,

95
00:08:51,136 --> 00:08:52,762
but you really should fix
that nasty habit.

96
00:08:52,846 --> 00:08:56,141
Pretty sure you were clinging to me
for dear life just moments ago.

97
00:08:56,224 --> 00:08:57,642
That was…

98
00:08:58,268 --> 00:08:59,477
I had my reasons.

99
00:08:59,561 --> 00:09:01,396
I get it. I'm sure with a face like mine,

100
00:09:01,479 --> 00:09:02,981
resisting such an urge can't be easy.

101
00:09:03,064 --> 00:09:05,358
You are spewing
an impressive load of crap.

102
00:09:06,151 --> 00:09:08,903
They went up here!
The Possessed Royal Consort girl.

103
00:09:10,572 --> 00:09:12,198
What a cursed day.

104
00:09:12,282 --> 00:09:14,284
These wretched gnats keep turning up.

105
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:16,911
Damn it.

106
00:09:19,289 --> 00:09:21,499
You're nothing but trouble. What now?

107
00:09:21,583 --> 00:09:23,418
I will signal you before I faint.
Carry me.

108
00:09:23,501 --> 00:09:25,920
-Carry you?
-What can they do to an unconscious woman?

109
00:09:26,004 --> 00:09:28,464
Especially a poor, helpless woman like me.

110
00:09:28,548 --> 00:09:29,924
Are you nuts? Why would I do that?

111
00:09:30,008 --> 00:09:31,134
There they are!

112
00:09:31,217 --> 00:09:33,261
They beat someone up and ran off!

113
00:09:37,724 --> 00:09:39,184
Someone's collapsed here!

114
00:09:40,518 --> 00:09:42,896
We have a sick person here!

115
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:46,065
Someone just fainted!
Call for an ambulance!

116
00:09:46,649 --> 00:09:47,650
Call for an ambulance now!

117
00:09:47,734 --> 00:09:49,277
Why did she faint?

118
00:09:50,236 --> 00:09:54,324
She and that man over there argued,
and she went into shock.

119
00:09:54,407 --> 00:09:55,408
What the…

120
00:10:00,371 --> 00:10:01,789
I think she stopped breathing.

121
00:10:01,873 --> 00:10:03,291
Move. Help me.

122
00:10:03,917 --> 00:10:05,084
Help me! Hurry!

123
00:10:05,168 --> 00:10:06,294
Yeah, okay.

124
00:10:07,003 --> 00:10:08,254
Okay. Let me.

125
00:10:10,465 --> 00:10:12,383
Move! Do you want a corpse on the stairs?

126
00:10:12,467 --> 00:10:14,427
Get out of the way! All of you!

127
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:17,138
Shin Seo-ri, wake up.

128
00:10:17,931 --> 00:10:19,641
Shin Seo-ri, stay with me.

129
00:10:19,724 --> 00:10:20,892
Shin Seo-ri.

130
00:10:22,477 --> 00:10:23,645
Hey.

131
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:27,023
Wake up. Come on. You need to wake up.

132
00:10:30,193 --> 00:10:31,361
Degenerate!

133
00:10:37,367 --> 00:10:38,785
You are surprisingly quick-witted.

134
00:10:38,868 --> 00:10:39,911
Well done.

135
00:10:39,994 --> 00:10:41,996
You think I played along
for your approval?

136
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,249
I couldn't just get dragged down with you.

137
00:10:44,332 --> 00:10:47,085
What does it matter?
The end justifies the means.

138
00:10:48,294 --> 00:10:49,462
But…

139
00:10:50,213 --> 00:10:52,465
that man from before, what is he to you?

140
00:10:53,132 --> 00:10:54,217
Who?

141
00:10:56,344 --> 00:10:57,595
-Mun-do?
-Is he your brother?

142
00:10:58,888 --> 00:11:01,349
Let's just say we're worse than strangers.

143
00:11:01,432 --> 00:11:02,684
Is that so?

144
00:11:03,643 --> 00:11:06,312
Then you can tell me
all about it on the way.

145
00:11:06,854 --> 00:11:08,940
On the way where? Hey!

146
00:11:09,023 --> 00:11:10,525
You wanted a contract, no?

147
00:11:10,608 --> 00:11:12,819
I was separated from my companion,
with no way back anyway.

148
00:11:12,902 --> 00:11:13,945
This is perfect.

149
00:11:14,904 --> 00:11:16,572
Do I look like your chauffeur?

150
00:11:17,532 --> 00:11:19,242
-Get out now.
-Don't be like that.

151
00:11:20,076 --> 00:11:21,953
-Get out.
-Why, you scoundrel.

152
00:11:22,036 --> 00:11:24,289
I hear she left
without so much as an apology?

153
00:11:24,372 --> 00:11:26,082
Yeah, but you know what's weird?

154
00:11:26,165 --> 00:11:28,543
I saw Cha Se-gye chase after her.

155
00:11:28,626 --> 00:11:30,962
-Cha Se-gye did?
-Yeah.

156
00:11:35,508 --> 00:11:37,176
Do I look like a taxi service to you?

157
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:40,013
You can't just get in this car
whenever you want.

158
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:43,349
Were you not the one
begging me to sign a contract?

159
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:44,434
So arrogant.

160
00:11:44,517 --> 00:11:46,227
Begging? Who was beg--

161
00:11:47,895 --> 00:11:50,148
I'll just have Mr. Son deliver it to you.

162
00:11:50,231 --> 00:11:52,525
If you have any common sense,
sign it and send it back.

163
00:11:52,608 --> 00:11:55,486
I'll drop you off at that subway stop.
Please get out this time.

164
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:57,447
You might as well take me all the way.

165
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:58,489
So heartless.

166
00:12:01,284 --> 00:12:02,618
Can I get a bowl of water?

167
00:12:02,702 --> 00:12:04,329
Why are you looking for water here?

168
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:09,876
What is it?

169
00:12:10,835 --> 00:12:11,753
What's wrong with you?

170
00:12:11,836 --> 00:12:14,672
I get nauseous every time I ride
in one of these iron palanquins.

171
00:12:14,756 --> 00:12:17,675
I feel like I have a knot
sitting in my gut.

172
00:12:19,594 --> 00:12:20,887
Don't you dare.

173
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:22,513
This car isn't even a month old yet.

174
00:12:22,597 --> 00:12:23,639
Don't you dare throw up.

175
00:12:25,016 --> 00:12:26,351
How can a man be this petty?

176
00:12:26,434 --> 00:12:28,227
Just drive slower.

177
00:12:28,895 --> 00:12:29,854
Damn it.

178
00:12:30,563 --> 00:12:31,647
Seriously?

179
00:12:31,731 --> 00:12:34,609
Must you snap at me every time I speak?

180
00:12:35,151 --> 00:12:36,194
You should see a doctor.

181
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:37,695
You desperately need some therapy.

182
00:12:37,779 --> 00:12:41,157
Were you in my shoes,
you would be on edge all the time as well.

183
00:12:59,217 --> 00:13:01,511
Hello, sir. How much would you like?

184
00:13:01,594 --> 00:13:04,055
-Fill it up.
-You got it.

185
00:13:20,071 --> 00:13:23,116
I get nauseous every time I ride
in one of these iron palanquins.

186
00:13:23,199 --> 00:13:26,077
I feel like I have a knot
sitting in my gut.

187
00:13:29,956 --> 00:13:33,418
As if she can win anybody over
with those cheap crocodile tears.

188
00:13:39,924 --> 00:13:41,217
DIGESTIVE AID

189
00:13:49,183 --> 00:13:50,393
Have I lost my mind?

190
00:13:50,476 --> 00:13:51,644
Why would I even buy that?

191
00:13:55,356 --> 00:13:56,315
Excuse me.

192
00:13:56,399 --> 00:13:58,276
If you're not buying that, could I…

193
00:13:59,652 --> 00:14:00,570
I'm not buying it.

194
00:14:00,653 --> 00:14:01,988
Who said I was buying it?

195
00:14:10,621 --> 00:14:12,874
What a truly marvelous world.

196
00:14:13,916 --> 00:14:16,711
This heavy iron palanquin
moves all by itself.

197
00:14:18,379 --> 00:14:20,673
And what purpose does this serve?

198
00:14:33,394 --> 00:14:34,812
The Ten-Second Listener Pop Quiz!

199
00:14:34,896 --> 00:14:36,105
Answer three questions right,

200
00:14:36,189 --> 00:14:38,608
and win yourself
a premium Hoengseong Beef set.

201
00:14:38,691 --> 00:14:40,276
-Beef?
-Here's the next question.

202
00:14:40,359 --> 00:14:42,236
What do you call the small wooden chest

203
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,322
used to store grains like rice?

204
00:14:44,405 --> 00:14:45,573
-A rice chest?
-Correct!

205
00:14:46,199 --> 00:14:47,325
General Choe Yeong said this.

206
00:14:47,408 --> 00:14:49,619
"Treat blank like stone."

207
00:14:49,702 --> 00:14:50,953
-Women?
-Wrong.

208
00:14:51,037 --> 00:14:53,873
Not women. The correct answer is
"Treat gold like stone."

209
00:14:53,956 --> 00:14:55,416
You were so close.

210
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:58,878
Unfortunately, you won't get the beef,
but you will get a set of coffee vouchers.

211
00:14:58,961 --> 00:15:00,171
Damn degenerate.

212
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:04,258
He said he was getting gas.
Is he refining it himself?

213
00:15:06,802 --> 00:15:08,763
PRESIDENT CHOI MUN-DO WINS
KOREA BUSINESSMAN AWARD

214
00:15:19,565 --> 00:15:22,443
How can two faces look so identical?

215
00:15:23,152 --> 00:15:25,905
He cannot be inhabiting
a look-alike's body like I am.

216
00:15:28,157 --> 00:15:30,034
Since he's a Choi and not a Yi…

217
00:15:31,953 --> 00:15:33,412
perhaps his mother is a Yi?

218
00:15:33,496 --> 00:15:35,623
CHAIL E&amp;C STOCK HITS NEW HIGH
FOLLOWING SCANDAL

219
00:15:38,918 --> 00:15:40,795
Let's just say we're worse than strangers.

220
00:15:40,878 --> 00:15:42,964
So he is related to Degenerate.

221
00:15:43,839 --> 00:15:46,092
They say cursed ties bind deeper
than destined ones.

222
00:15:46,175 --> 00:15:47,593
HOW THE LEADERS OF CHAIL GROUP COMPARE

223
00:15:47,677 --> 00:15:49,554
My intuition is never wrong.

224
00:15:49,637 --> 00:15:53,558
When it feels off, it is best to avoid it.

225
00:15:56,852 --> 00:15:58,646
-Excuse me! Hey!
-What is it?

226
00:15:58,729 --> 00:16:00,773
Don't forget this.
Your boyfriend left his card.

227
00:16:00,856 --> 00:16:01,774
Here.

228
00:16:12,410 --> 00:16:14,287
DIGESTIVE AID

229
00:16:16,372 --> 00:16:18,958
I mean, I would provide this to anybody.

230
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:22,753
On humanitarian grounds,
for a potential contracting party.

231
00:16:22,837 --> 00:16:25,214
This falls well
within the realm of possibility.

232
00:16:26,465 --> 00:16:27,341
Where'd she go?

233
00:16:29,468 --> 00:16:31,470
Is she off throwing up somewhere?

234
00:16:32,471 --> 00:16:35,141
Excuse me, did you see where
the woman who was just here went?

235
00:16:35,224 --> 00:16:37,476
She rushed off not too long ago.

236
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,604
I gave the card to your girlfriend.

237
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,692
She took my card and ran?

238
00:16:46,611 --> 00:16:48,863
Unbelievable. This woman…

239
00:16:50,823 --> 00:16:53,034
Hey, Mr. Son. I found Shin Seo-ri.

240
00:16:53,117 --> 00:16:54,910
But she just ran off with my card--

241
00:16:54,994 --> 00:16:56,454
Sir, we have a huge problem.

242
00:16:59,749 --> 00:17:00,791
How did this happen?

243
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:03,544
Kaiserman Capital, the company
we brought in for the new brand launch,

244
00:17:03,628 --> 00:17:06,255
is tied to Chail E&amp;C,
according to our legal team.

245
00:17:06,339 --> 00:17:09,550
Today's updated regulatory filing
from Chail E&amp;C leads to one conclusion.

246
00:17:09,634 --> 00:17:13,137
Kaiserman's majority shareholder
and President Choi are one and the same.

247
00:17:13,220 --> 00:17:14,597
What should we do now?

248
00:17:16,432 --> 00:17:18,351
What else?
We put out the urgent fires first.

249
00:17:18,434 --> 00:17:20,478
Call an emergency board meeting now.

250
00:17:28,235 --> 00:17:31,197
Oh dear. It looks like things have
already been turned upside down.

251
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:35,534
He must've found out that Kaiserman,
his savior, was actually a virus.

252
00:17:35,618 --> 00:17:37,745
How will you proceed?

253
00:17:37,828 --> 00:17:41,082
For now, we'll have to wait and see
how Cha Se-gye responds.

254
00:17:41,165 --> 00:17:42,875
We have no reason to rush.

255
00:17:43,459 --> 00:17:47,046
No. However, there has been
a minor development

256
00:17:47,129 --> 00:17:48,756
in Mr. Cha's personal life.

257
00:17:48,839 --> 00:17:49,924
A woman, you mean?

258
00:17:50,007 --> 00:17:51,926
Of course you already knew.

259
00:17:52,009 --> 00:17:54,929
She auditioned to be
Dynaestie's spokesperson.

260
00:17:55,012 --> 00:17:57,556
It seemed like
they already knew each other.

261
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,433
What are you doing here?

262
00:17:59,517 --> 00:18:02,269
He was with some woman earlier as well.

263
00:18:02,353 --> 00:18:04,855
I went to give him a heads-up
and found them together,

264
00:18:04,939 --> 00:18:06,941
looking rather intimate.

265
00:18:07,024 --> 00:18:08,192
"Audition"?

266
00:18:08,984 --> 00:18:09,860
She's a celebrity?

267
00:18:09,944 --> 00:18:12,154
From what I dug up, she's obscure at best.

268
00:18:12,238 --> 00:18:14,573
Just an unknown actress. Nothing special.

269
00:18:15,199 --> 00:18:17,993
A no-name actress and Cha Se-gye.

270
00:18:18,077 --> 00:18:20,121
What an amusing pair.

271
00:18:21,622 --> 00:18:24,333
Stop worrying. I'm doing great.

272
00:18:24,417 --> 00:18:27,002
Okay, I'm hanging up now.

273
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,714
Hey, what was all that earlier?

274
00:18:29,797 --> 00:18:31,674
You put me in a really awkward position.

275
00:18:31,757 --> 00:18:33,467
As if you had it worse than me.

276
00:18:33,551 --> 00:18:36,345
I followed you to make some money
and nearly crossed into the afterlife.

277
00:18:36,429 --> 00:18:38,013
That's enough chit-chat. Give me my pay.

278
00:18:38,097 --> 00:18:39,974
Pay? You've got to be kidding…

279
00:18:40,057 --> 00:18:41,767
You just ran off
after making such a scene,

280
00:18:41,851 --> 00:18:43,185
and you expect to be paid?

281
00:18:43,269 --> 00:18:45,646
You should be grateful
I'm not asking for damages.

282
00:18:45,730 --> 00:18:47,940
So you got swindled?

283
00:18:48,482 --> 00:18:50,151
What an idiot.

284
00:18:50,234 --> 00:18:51,277
Get back inside!

285
00:18:53,112 --> 00:18:54,363
-Got it!
-What the…

286
00:18:54,864 --> 00:18:56,449
What do you think you're doing?

287
00:18:56,532 --> 00:18:58,617
I see you made sure to collect your share.

288
00:18:58,701 --> 00:19:00,411
Not even a shred of loyalty to be found.

289
00:19:00,494 --> 00:19:02,329
Survival comes first. Give it back!

290
00:19:02,413 --> 00:19:03,998
All right. Fine.

291
00:19:04,081 --> 00:19:06,917
Out of the goodness of my heart,
I will just take half.

292
00:19:07,585 --> 00:19:10,254
My heart is too soft for its own good.

293
00:19:10,796 --> 00:19:12,256
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

294
00:19:12,381 --> 00:19:13,382
Unbelievable.

295
00:19:13,466 --> 00:19:15,468
What a wicked woman.

296
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:18,471
Damn it.

297
00:19:21,849 --> 00:19:26,187
Has the source claiming Kaiserman Capital
is tied to Chail E&amp;C been verified?

298
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:28,022
It's known to be an LP for Chail E&amp;C,

299
00:19:28,105 --> 00:19:30,274
but it's most likely
a borrowed-name account.

300
00:19:30,357 --> 00:19:32,359
And the person behind that account

301
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,487
is Choi Mun-do.

302
00:19:35,905 --> 00:19:37,990
What was the conversion price
the fund proposed?

303
00:19:38,073 --> 00:19:38,991
It was 50,000 won.

304
00:19:39,074 --> 00:19:41,619
It's holding support around 90,000 won,

305
00:19:41,702 --> 00:19:43,412
but if it drops below 50,000 won,

306
00:19:43,496 --> 00:19:46,457
they can refix the price
or demand repayment.

307
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:49,919
So basically,
if it drops below 50,000 won,

308
00:19:51,045 --> 00:19:52,338
they'll scoop up everything?

309
00:19:52,421 --> 00:19:55,508
And if Kaiserman converts
the bonds to stocks--

310
00:19:55,591 --> 00:19:58,177
Kaiserman becomes

311
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:00,387
Biojei's largest shareholder.

312
00:20:00,471 --> 00:20:02,223
That is quite a solid sucker punch.

313
00:20:06,393 --> 00:20:07,603
Hey.

314
00:20:09,355 --> 00:20:11,607
If you wanted to invest,
you should've just said so.

315
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:12,775
What is this?

316
00:20:12,858 --> 00:20:14,485
Se-gye, calm down.

317
00:20:14,568 --> 00:20:16,028
Since when was legally investing

318
00:20:16,111 --> 00:20:18,447
in a promising startup
considered problematic?

319
00:20:18,531 --> 00:20:21,408
I felt sorry for you,
obsessed with your self-made man act.

320
00:20:21,492 --> 00:20:23,035
So I helped you out a bit.

321
00:20:23,118 --> 00:20:24,328
Why are you so angry?

322
00:20:27,665 --> 00:20:28,958
You can cut the act with me.

323
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,793
Your hypocrisy makes me sick.

324
00:20:34,421 --> 00:20:35,965
So touchy.

325
00:20:36,048 --> 00:20:37,383
Look, you…

326
00:20:39,343 --> 00:20:40,636
That's why you'll never succeed.

327
00:20:40,719 --> 00:20:44,098
You're a complete amateur
with nothing but pedigree for credentials.

328
00:20:50,604 --> 00:20:52,439
Are you talking about yourself?

329
00:20:52,523 --> 00:20:55,693
I couldn't care less
about your grand ambitions for Chail.

330
00:20:55,776 --> 00:20:58,445
If you're thinking about messing around
with the shares in my company,

331
00:20:58,529 --> 00:20:59,905
you can just forget it.

332
00:20:59,989 --> 00:21:03,909
You could end up losing
everything you've built in an instant.

333
00:21:04,535 --> 00:21:05,786
I see.

334
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:07,997
Is that a threat?

335
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:09,957
But will I even get the chance to?

336
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,917
Power trips and executive scandals
at every turn.

337
00:21:12,001 --> 00:21:14,378
You're bound to crumble without my help.

338
00:21:14,461 --> 00:21:15,838
So know your place,

339
00:21:15,921 --> 00:21:18,716
and just worry
about your pathetic little company.

340
00:21:18,799 --> 00:21:20,551
Just keep doing what you're doing.

341
00:21:20,634 --> 00:21:24,138
Make sure you keep up your act too,
so Grandfather never finds out.

342
00:21:24,221 --> 00:21:27,850
He relies on you so much.
Just imagine how disappointed he'd be.

343
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,686
Don't you think?

344
00:21:46,035 --> 00:21:47,494
It was my mistake.

345
00:21:47,578 --> 00:21:49,079
I should've been more thorough.

346
00:21:49,163 --> 00:21:50,497
I never thought President Choi--

347
00:21:50,581 --> 00:21:54,126
It's fine. Backstabbing has been
his MO since day one.

348
00:21:54,209 --> 00:21:56,921
In this world, you're either
an ally or an enemy, nothing in between.

349
00:21:57,004 --> 00:22:00,382
First and foremost,
you need to watch out for hypocrites.

350
00:22:00,466 --> 00:22:01,550
This is Mun-do.

351
00:22:01,634 --> 00:22:05,888
He may be a distant cousin,
but treat him as a brother.

352
00:22:05,971 --> 00:22:09,016
To a seven-year-old kid,
he seemed like a reliable ally.

353
00:22:09,642 --> 00:22:11,769
Hi, Se-gye. It's nice to meet you.

354
00:22:11,852 --> 00:22:14,813
A kind ally on my side
in a suffocating world

355
00:22:14,897 --> 00:22:16,649
full of adults.

356
00:22:25,449 --> 00:22:26,492
Brother.

357
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:30,871
Want some?

358
00:22:34,708 --> 00:22:36,168
Who said I was your brother?

359
00:22:36,794 --> 00:22:37,962
What…

360
00:22:39,838 --> 00:22:41,256
Se-gye!

361
00:22:48,472 --> 00:22:50,516
My goodness, what happened?

362
00:22:50,599 --> 00:22:52,726
Se-gye, I'm so sorry.

363
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:55,229
All I wanted was
to get to know you better.

364
00:22:55,312 --> 00:22:58,440
Uncle, it's okay. I'm not hurt badly.

365
00:23:00,401 --> 00:23:03,362
Oh dear. Goodness me.

366
00:23:05,364 --> 00:23:06,824
Where did you learn your manners?

367
00:23:10,285 --> 00:23:12,830
I have no need
for a foolish brat like you!

368
00:23:28,345 --> 00:23:31,306
I learned the hard way that in this world,

369
00:23:31,390 --> 00:23:32,975
the weak get trampled.

370
00:23:33,058 --> 00:23:34,184
How should we proceed?

371
00:23:34,268 --> 00:23:36,395
As it stands, we can't withdraw
the funds right away.

372
00:23:36,478 --> 00:23:40,107
Why pull them out?
We need to milk this for all it's worth.

373
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:44,069
For now, let's get all hands on deck
and move up the launch timeline.

374
00:23:45,863 --> 00:23:48,615
What about the ad campaign?

375
00:23:48,699 --> 00:23:50,534
Can we proceed with Ms. Shin?

376
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:56,582
I can't stand women who cry.

377
00:23:56,665 --> 00:23:57,833
Pardon?

378
00:23:58,876 --> 00:24:02,254
We obviously need to revisit that.
Protecting our image comes first.

379
00:24:07,384 --> 00:24:09,511
Sir, are you experiencing
digestive issues?

380
00:24:09,595 --> 00:24:10,596
Oh, that?

381
00:24:11,722 --> 00:24:13,182
I was for a second earlier.

382
00:24:15,267 --> 00:24:17,686
I'm beginning to think
this car has poor ride quality.

383
00:24:17,770 --> 00:24:20,355
Ms. Shin also asked me
to slow down earlier.

384
00:24:20,439 --> 00:24:22,691
She got super pale
and said she felt terribly nauseous.

385
00:24:22,775 --> 00:24:24,777
Why are you telling me this now?

386
00:24:25,819 --> 00:24:29,490
I didn't think I needed to report
that she was carsick.

387
00:24:37,122 --> 00:24:38,540
That woman…

388
00:24:39,291 --> 00:24:41,710
She probably hasn't even eaten yet.

389
00:24:47,341 --> 00:24:48,801
This is to die for.

390
00:24:48,884 --> 00:24:51,095
Hard work makes food taste like honey.

391
00:24:53,388 --> 00:24:55,140
Why are you so dressed up this late?

392
00:24:55,224 --> 00:24:58,227
Stop wasting time on lost causes
and come have a bite.

393
00:24:58,310 --> 00:25:00,145
I seasoned it just right.

394
00:25:00,646 --> 00:25:01,647
Wow.

395
00:25:03,023 --> 00:25:05,317
You enjoy all that, Unit 203.

396
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,820
I'm off to put a knife to good use today.

397
00:25:12,366 --> 00:25:15,035
A knife? Is he on his way
to carve some meat?

398
00:25:16,995 --> 00:25:18,205
That disloyal jerk.

399
00:25:18,831 --> 00:25:20,207
Hope you choke on your food.

400
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:21,458
I'm getting married.

401
00:25:24,753 --> 00:25:27,464
Min-a, are you really going
to make me the bad guy?

402
00:25:27,548 --> 00:25:29,550
At least let me be the one to propose.

403
00:25:29,633 --> 00:25:31,218
No. Not you.

404
00:25:36,974 --> 00:25:38,350
BRIDE: MIN-A
GROOM: GYEONG-SU

405
00:25:41,854 --> 00:25:44,273
So that's what it was.
You were cheating on me.

406
00:25:44,356 --> 00:25:46,191
You've always been a little dense.

407
00:25:46,275 --> 00:25:48,235
You used to say that was my charm.

408
00:25:48,318 --> 00:25:50,529
I would've fixed it if you'd told me.

409
00:25:50,612 --> 00:25:52,990
It's not like it's a disease.
How could you fix it?

410
00:25:53,073 --> 00:25:54,867
Nothing's impossible
if you try hard enough.

411
00:25:54,950 --> 00:25:56,410
Some things are. You're still jobless.

412
00:25:56,493 --> 00:25:59,621
If effort were all it took,
we wouldn't have ended up like this.

413
00:25:59,705 --> 00:26:01,540
So your cheating was self-preservation?

414
00:26:12,384 --> 00:26:14,678
I wouldn't waste coffee like that.

415
00:26:15,345 --> 00:26:17,472
I'm not that kind of person.

416
00:26:20,309 --> 00:26:21,310
Seven thousand won.

417
00:26:21,393 --> 00:26:23,270
Seven thousand won? Hold on.

418
00:26:24,271 --> 00:26:25,647
8 FOR 3,500 WON

419
00:26:26,481 --> 00:26:27,774
Jeez.

420
00:26:28,901 --> 00:26:31,445
When did these confections
get so expensive?

421
00:26:31,528 --> 00:26:33,780
Miss, are you short on cash?

422
00:26:33,864 --> 00:26:35,949
We take cards too.

423
00:26:36,033 --> 00:26:36,909
Cards?

424
00:26:36,992 --> 00:26:39,203
That thing in your hand.

425
00:26:39,286 --> 00:26:41,330
If that's not a card, what is it?

426
00:26:42,331 --> 00:26:43,874
You mean this?

427
00:26:43,957 --> 00:26:45,250
Paying in full, right?

428
00:26:46,251 --> 00:26:47,127
CONFIRM TRANSACTION

429
00:26:51,632 --> 00:26:53,425
Go on. Take it.

430
00:26:54,218 --> 00:26:57,763
So I can pay with this
instead of cash.

431
00:26:57,846 --> 00:26:59,431
-Is that it?
-Yes.

432
00:27:00,724 --> 00:27:03,393
Then give me eight more bags,
for a total of ten.

433
00:27:06,521 --> 00:27:08,190
AMOUNT: 28,000 WON

434
00:27:12,736 --> 00:27:13,612
What's this?

435
00:27:13,695 --> 00:27:14,863
DOLI MANJOOS: 7,000 WON

436
00:27:15,614 --> 00:27:16,740
DOLI MANJOOS: 28,000 WON

437
00:27:16,823 --> 00:27:17,741
KONG KONG BEAD ICE CREAM: 4,000 WON

438
00:27:18,408 --> 00:27:19,493
"Twisted doughnuts…"

439
00:27:20,327 --> 00:27:21,620
"Yum Yum Tanghulu."

440
00:27:24,665 --> 00:27:26,416
CHIEF OF STAFF SON JAE-HAN

441
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,713
Yes, sir. How may I help you?

442
00:27:31,797 --> 00:27:34,508
Mr. Son, didn't I tell you
to suspend my card?

443
00:27:34,591 --> 00:27:36,885
It's been so hectic. I completely forgot.

444
00:27:36,969 --> 00:27:38,470
My apologies. I'll handle it tomorrow.

445
00:27:38,553 --> 00:27:42,099
Don't I pay you
that industry-leading salary to cover

446
00:27:42,182 --> 00:27:44,935
for the rare slip-ups I make
about once a year?

447
00:27:45,018 --> 00:27:46,603
Forget it. I'll go get it myself.

448
00:27:46,687 --> 00:27:50,190
Sir, you can report a lost credit card
over the phone 24/7.

449
00:27:50,774 --> 00:27:52,401
No, that woman.

450
00:27:52,484 --> 00:27:54,653
Send me Shin Seo-ri's address.

451
00:28:02,828 --> 00:28:03,870
Wait.

452
00:28:04,913 --> 00:28:06,081
Hey!

453
00:28:07,541 --> 00:28:09,543
How deep could the conversation be

454
00:28:09,626 --> 00:28:11,420
for him to not even hear that?

455
00:28:15,173 --> 00:28:16,967
Let's end it here.

456
00:28:17,634 --> 00:28:18,844
I'm going to head out.

457
00:28:19,594 --> 00:28:20,846
Min-a, wait.

458
00:28:20,929 --> 00:28:22,431
Can you hold out your hands?

459
00:28:23,056 --> 00:28:24,099
Why?

460
00:28:43,076 --> 00:28:45,704
What the… What was that?

461
00:28:45,787 --> 00:28:48,040
Imagining you meeting his parents
with the bag I bought you

462
00:28:48,123 --> 00:28:50,042
made my blood suddenly boil.

463
00:28:53,003 --> 00:28:54,504
Wait, just a second.

464
00:28:57,674 --> 00:28:58,800
I get that you're angry.

465
00:28:58,884 --> 00:29:01,720
I never wanted to be labeled
as an opportunist anyway.

466
00:29:01,803 --> 00:29:03,013
It's actually better this way.

467
00:29:03,096 --> 00:29:05,474
Since this will probably be
our last meeting,

468
00:29:06,099 --> 00:29:07,726
let's end this properly.

469
00:29:19,237 --> 00:29:22,574
My word. Just look at them.

470
00:29:27,996 --> 00:29:29,706
Are you sure this is her address?

471
00:29:31,208 --> 00:29:32,793
Who knew my neighborhood
had such slums?

472
00:29:32,876 --> 00:29:34,503
Yes. Same town, different world.

473
00:29:34,586 --> 00:29:36,797
The place with the peeling paint.
That's it.

474
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:38,632
It's even more pathetic than I expected.

475
00:29:38,715 --> 00:29:39,841
Thanks.

476
00:29:45,138 --> 00:29:47,265
Even after 300 years,

477
00:29:47,349 --> 00:29:50,560
affairs of the heart still end in squalor.

478
00:29:53,021 --> 00:29:55,107
Should I pretend
I just found this on the street?

479
00:29:55,190 --> 00:29:56,608
That's quite an outdated line.

480
00:29:59,444 --> 00:30:00,570
What are you doing here?

481
00:30:00,654 --> 00:30:02,614
How did you know where I live?

482
00:30:02,697 --> 00:30:04,908
Do not tell me you were tailing me.

483
00:30:04,991 --> 00:30:07,369
As if I'd even need to tail you
to find your address.

484
00:30:07,452 --> 00:30:09,121
Mr. Son drove you home before.

485
00:30:11,123 --> 00:30:13,834
Oh, right. He did do that.

486
00:30:14,501 --> 00:30:17,629
I hear you insisted he escort me home
because you were worried.

487
00:30:18,130 --> 00:30:19,923
Worried? Me?

488
00:30:20,006 --> 00:30:21,633
No need to be coy about it.

489
00:30:21,716 --> 00:30:24,052
Even a degenerate like you is still human.

490
00:30:24,136 --> 00:30:26,096
Decency has not entirely left you.

491
00:30:26,179 --> 00:30:27,973
Glad to know it is not
for personal reasons.

492
00:30:29,266 --> 00:30:32,018
As if I could ever have
such feelings for you.

493
00:30:32,102 --> 00:30:34,980
A woman who still splurges
on designer bags despite her situation.

494
00:30:35,063 --> 00:30:36,356
What about my situation?

495
00:30:37,941 --> 00:30:39,943
Are you here this late
just to pick a fight?

496
00:30:40,026 --> 00:30:43,029
It appears that contract or whatever
has you all worked up.

497
00:30:43,113 --> 00:30:45,740
I cannot simply bind myself
to just any arrangement, can I?

498
00:30:45,824 --> 00:30:47,492
I must go over it with a fine-tooth comb.

499
00:30:47,576 --> 00:30:51,037
I shall decide after carefully weighing
the upside and downside.

500
00:30:51,121 --> 00:30:53,915
You're a TNT.
You can't really afford to be picky.

501
00:30:54,875 --> 00:30:56,543
"TNT"?

502
00:30:57,294 --> 00:30:58,170
And what is that?

503
00:30:59,212 --> 00:31:01,256
No money, no credentials, no sense.

504
00:31:01,339 --> 00:31:03,175
The no-name actor with no real work.

505
00:31:03,258 --> 00:31:06,720
For a "Triple Non-Threat" actor like you,
this is like winning the lottery.

506
00:31:06,803 --> 00:31:10,098
Did you just come here
to rub all my shortcomings in my face?

507
00:31:14,352 --> 00:31:15,270
Just hand over my card.

508
00:31:16,271 --> 00:31:17,772
-What card?
-The ca--

509
00:31:19,399 --> 00:31:20,567
The card.

510
00:31:24,905 --> 00:31:25,947
Wait.

511
00:31:26,907 --> 00:31:31,203
This magical item?
This goblin's club belonged to you?

512
00:31:31,995 --> 00:31:33,872
How does one acquire such a fine thing?

513
00:31:33,955 --> 00:31:35,790
You need to be creditworthy.

514
00:31:35,874 --> 00:31:37,792
Is that so?

515
00:31:37,876 --> 00:31:39,753
When it comes to credibility,
I am second to none.

516
00:31:39,836 --> 00:31:41,421
At just the mere mention of my name,

517
00:31:41,505 --> 00:31:43,757
even wealthy landowners put up
their fields as collateral.

518
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:47,427
Come sunrise,
I must make a dozen or so for myself.

519
00:31:47,511 --> 00:31:48,428
Here.

520
00:31:48,512 --> 00:31:50,388
Are you looking to run
a credit card scheme now?

521
00:31:50,472 --> 00:31:51,556
Knock yourself out.

522
00:32:01,650 --> 00:32:04,569
Are you really living off
stuff like that for your meals?

523
00:32:06,238 --> 00:32:07,822
Are you that strapped for cash?

524
00:32:11,952 --> 00:32:15,288
If I say no, he will probably have me
repay every bit of it.

525
00:32:15,372 --> 00:32:16,581
Yes. I am beyond strapped.

526
00:32:16,665 --> 00:32:18,750
I can barely afford to eat. So what?

527
00:32:22,128 --> 00:32:23,088
Is it really that bad?

528
00:32:30,428 --> 00:32:32,514
That's why you should try
to make an honest living.

529
00:32:32,597 --> 00:32:34,808
Put that perfectly good body to use.

530
00:32:36,017 --> 00:32:37,978
Where is that savory aroma coming from?

531
00:32:42,607 --> 00:32:44,109
YEONJEONG GALBI

532
00:32:46,736 --> 00:32:47,946
Jesus.

533
00:32:55,412 --> 00:32:56,621
What's with that look?

534
00:32:58,331 --> 00:32:59,457
What are you expecting?

535
00:33:01,042 --> 00:33:02,252
Do you think I'm nuts?

536
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,221
Since I'm paying, you cook.

537
00:33:13,305 --> 00:33:14,973
Look at you expecting royal treatment.

538
00:33:15,056 --> 00:33:18,852
You picked up the tongs so naturally.
I thought grilling meat was your hobby.

539
00:33:18,935 --> 00:33:20,186
They are ready. Help yourself.

540
00:33:20,270 --> 00:33:23,148
People might think
you're the one picking up the tab here.

541
00:33:24,399 --> 00:33:26,484
Even a stray dog has its own name.

542
00:33:26,568 --> 00:33:28,528
It's Shin Seo-ri, not "you."

543
00:33:28,612 --> 00:33:31,406
I'm Cha Se-gye, not "Degenerate."

544
00:33:32,073 --> 00:33:33,617
Right. Cha Se-gye.

545
00:33:33,700 --> 00:33:36,870
Now that we are introduced,
enough with the formalities. Eat.

546
00:33:36,953 --> 00:33:40,165
The meat is so tender.
It is quite palatable.

547
00:33:41,541 --> 00:33:45,086
You should be calling me
Mr. Cha Se-gye or sir.

548
00:33:45,170 --> 00:33:48,298
So sensitive about titles.
You must be obsessed with rank.

549
00:33:48,381 --> 00:33:50,258
I hear they call
people like you "boomers."

550
00:33:50,342 --> 00:33:52,344
You're one to talk with that bossy tone.

551
00:33:52,427 --> 00:33:54,387
That piece is about to burn. Flip it.

552
00:34:01,978 --> 00:34:05,857
I must have been destined
to eat this beef today.

553
00:34:08,109 --> 00:34:09,986
Destiny? Over something so trivial.

554
00:34:10,070 --> 00:34:12,947
In your iron palanquin today,
I heard an interesting quiz.

555
00:34:13,031 --> 00:34:16,076
The prize was a beef set,
but sadly, I did not win it.

556
00:34:16,159 --> 00:34:18,411
However, the beef I lost
made its way back to me.

557
00:34:18,495 --> 00:34:19,996
How could this not be destiny?

558
00:34:20,747 --> 00:34:23,333
If the beef was destiny,
was I inescapable fate?

559
00:34:23,416 --> 00:34:24,334
What was that?

560
00:34:29,047 --> 00:34:31,091
I mean, think about it.

561
00:34:31,174 --> 00:34:34,219
How many times have we run
into each other by chance?

562
00:34:34,302 --> 00:34:38,056
And it's not like I'll ever be compensated
for doing this charitable act.

563
00:34:38,139 --> 00:34:39,140
Compensation?

564
00:34:40,684 --> 00:34:41,893
Come to think of it,

565
00:34:41,976 --> 00:34:44,145
had I not had the misfortune
of running into you today,

566
00:34:44,229 --> 00:34:46,523
I could have used the wages
I was due to buy myself

567
00:34:46,606 --> 00:34:48,566
not just one serving,
but a whole crate of beef.

568
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:52,570
By that logic, this is a reward
bestowed upon me by the heavens.

569
00:34:53,446 --> 00:34:56,908
Wow, what miraculous logic.

570
00:34:56,991 --> 00:34:59,369
Shin Seo-ri, your selective morals
are mind-blowing.

571
00:34:59,452 --> 00:35:00,829
What is mind-blowing?

572
00:35:01,663 --> 00:35:03,498
You know about boomers,
but not selective morals?

573
00:35:03,581 --> 00:35:05,709
"Romance when it's me,
adultery when it's anyone else."

574
00:35:05,792 --> 00:35:07,210
I get the adultery part.

575
00:35:07,752 --> 00:35:09,379
But what is "romance"?

576
00:35:11,631 --> 00:35:12,716
I get it.

577
00:35:13,758 --> 00:35:15,802
Can't understand any English?
Is that your gimmick?

578
00:35:15,885 --> 00:35:19,264
Then again, it'd be weird
if a Joseon woman knew what "romance" was.

579
00:35:19,931 --> 00:35:22,016
You're really committed
to your method acting.

580
00:35:22,100 --> 00:35:24,144
So dedicated to your craft.

581
00:35:34,904 --> 00:35:38,074
I tried to keep my distance
since he is from the same family,

582
00:35:38,158 --> 00:35:41,703
but I was blinded by the beef
and lost my senses for a moment.

583
00:35:41,786 --> 00:35:42,787
Unbelievable.

584
00:35:44,539 --> 00:35:47,208
Your mukbang skills are on another level.

585
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:49,878
It's like you ate an entire cow.

586
00:35:49,961 --> 00:35:52,839
Do not exaggerate.
How could I eat a whole cow?

587
00:35:54,048 --> 00:35:57,635
You finished the first round with ribeye,
chuck flap, sirloin, and specialty cuts.

588
00:35:57,719 --> 00:36:01,556
Then you capped it all off with large
and small intestine for dessert.

589
00:36:02,348 --> 00:36:05,101
It was better than I expected.

590
00:36:05,977 --> 00:36:09,522
Who knew offal that even peasants
would not touch could be this savory?

591
00:36:09,606 --> 00:36:11,483
I have experienced a whole new world.

592
00:36:13,193 --> 00:36:14,819
I guess your stomach's feeling better now.

593
00:36:14,903 --> 00:36:17,030
It has been fine the whole time.

594
00:36:20,950 --> 00:36:22,827
You were worried about me again.

595
00:36:24,120 --> 00:36:25,038
Worried? As if.

596
00:36:25,663 --> 00:36:28,583
I have never once worried
about anyone but myself.

597
00:36:28,666 --> 00:36:30,710
My head's about to explode
from my own problems.

598
00:36:30,794 --> 00:36:33,588
This skirt has a generous waistband.
I quite like it.

599
00:36:37,675 --> 00:36:39,719
What a truly ridiculous woman.

600
00:36:44,098 --> 00:36:45,058
Mun-do.

601
00:36:45,558 --> 00:36:47,811
I hear you went to Sejong today?

602
00:36:47,894 --> 00:36:49,062
Yes, Uncle.

603
00:36:49,729 --> 00:36:51,856
They said I had to accept it in person.

604
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:54,359
Why hide it? If anything,
you should be bragging about it.

605
00:36:54,442 --> 00:36:57,862
I heard from Attorney Choi
that our company's stock hit

606
00:36:57,946 --> 00:36:59,864
an all-time high today, thanks to you.

607
00:36:59,948 --> 00:37:01,282
You did well.

608
00:37:01,825 --> 00:37:03,493
I didn't really do anything.

609
00:37:04,035 --> 00:37:06,579
I'm just following the path
that you paved for me.

610
00:37:06,663 --> 00:37:09,791
If only Se-gye were half the man you are,

611
00:37:09,874 --> 00:37:11,376
I would've retired early

612
00:37:11,459 --> 00:37:14,754
and just spent my days fishing like this.

613
00:37:14,838 --> 00:37:16,130
Come on now.

614
00:37:16,714 --> 00:37:20,385
Se-gye's startup is doing well,
and he seems a bit more at ease now.

615
00:37:20,468 --> 00:37:22,929
That kid is crazy about money.
He'll never be "at ease."

616
00:37:23,012 --> 00:37:25,890
He must be in a better headspace
if he's going on dates and stuff.

617
00:37:25,974 --> 00:37:27,225
Se-gye is seeing a girl?

618
00:37:27,308 --> 00:37:29,435
But he has impossibly high standards.

619
00:37:29,519 --> 00:37:30,770
What's she like?

620
00:37:31,271 --> 00:37:32,438
I don't know much, Uncle.

621
00:37:32,522 --> 00:37:35,191
I just caught a glimpse of them
when I stopped by the TV station.

622
00:37:35,275 --> 00:37:37,485
What? Did you say TV station?

623
00:37:38,069 --> 00:37:40,947
Then is she a news anchor?

624
00:37:44,868 --> 00:37:48,162
I shall give the contract
careful consideration.

625
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:51,791
You even bribed me with Korean beef.
What choice do I have?

626
00:37:51,875 --> 00:37:53,084
That wasn't a bribe.

627
00:37:54,919 --> 00:37:56,796
The beef was an act of charity.

628
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:59,340
Like the change I give
to the Salvation Army once a year.

629
00:37:59,424 --> 00:38:00,383
Nothing more.

630
00:38:00,466 --> 00:38:01,342
Sure. Why not?

631
00:38:01,426 --> 00:38:03,511
Do not worry.
I shall give it favorable consideration.

632
00:38:05,096 --> 00:38:06,764
Since you want me so badly.

633
00:38:06,848 --> 00:38:09,934
I will not be heartless
and just turn you away after beef.

634
00:38:10,018 --> 00:38:13,855
Hold on, but nothing
has been confirmed just yet.

635
00:38:18,234 --> 00:38:19,235
Forget it.

636
00:38:23,072 --> 00:38:25,700
Sell that designer bag so you can
at least eat for the time being.

637
00:38:25,783 --> 00:38:28,244
Stop eating junk food for every meal.

638
00:38:43,593 --> 00:38:46,179
Contrary to that icy exterior,

639
00:38:47,263 --> 00:38:49,349
he is a worrier at heart.

640
00:38:50,141 --> 00:38:51,392
Cha Se-gye.

641
00:39:08,618 --> 00:39:09,994
DIGESTIVE AID

642
00:39:11,996 --> 00:39:13,122
Damn it.

643
00:39:16,709 --> 00:39:19,253
That woman could easily eat
a whole cow by herself.

644
00:39:20,213 --> 00:39:21,464
She'll be fine.

645
00:39:22,090 --> 00:39:23,967
You were worried about me again.

646
00:39:24,050 --> 00:39:26,719
Why the hell would I worry
about that reckless woman?

647
00:39:29,263 --> 00:39:30,223
As if.

648
00:39:31,057 --> 00:39:33,559
Anyone can see

649
00:39:33,643 --> 00:39:36,229
This must be love

650
00:39:37,105 --> 00:39:38,189
You'd think

651
00:39:38,272 --> 00:39:41,442
We'd probably get tired of each other
After spending the whole day together

652
00:39:41,526 --> 00:39:42,443
HOUR OF LOVE

653
00:39:42,527 --> 00:39:43,403
LOVE FREQUENCY

654
00:39:43,486 --> 00:39:47,365
I knew I would fall in love

655
00:39:50,201 --> 00:39:54,038
On the day that we first met

656
00:39:58,543 --> 00:39:59,794
What's with this radio?

657
00:39:59,877 --> 00:40:02,005
Turn left ahead.

658
00:40:02,088 --> 00:40:05,091
Use the far-left lane.

659
00:40:06,009 --> 00:40:06,884
Jesus!

660
00:40:06,968 --> 00:40:07,885
LOVE…

661
00:40:11,264 --> 00:40:12,974
What the…

662
00:40:13,057 --> 00:40:14,767
LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT

663
00:40:19,063 --> 00:40:20,064
What was that?

664
00:40:20,148 --> 00:40:23,317
You are off route.
You are off route.

665
00:40:25,445 --> 00:40:27,321
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

666
00:40:32,702 --> 00:40:34,412
After bragging
about carving all that meat,

667
00:40:34,495 --> 00:40:37,165
you have the face of a man
unceremoniously cast aside.

668
00:40:37,915 --> 00:40:40,168
Just don't mess with me today.

669
00:40:40,793 --> 00:40:42,920
Wait. That bag…

670
00:40:43,004 --> 00:40:44,547
I found it out front.

671
00:40:46,090 --> 00:40:47,175
Is it yours?

672
00:40:47,258 --> 00:40:50,303
When it comes to love,
there's no yours or mine.

673
00:40:50,386 --> 00:40:52,638
Forget it. You can keep it
or toss it. I don't care.

674
00:40:52,722 --> 00:40:55,058
As if affection between men and women
were anything special.

675
00:40:55,141 --> 00:40:56,559
What a sorry excuse for a man.

676
00:40:56,642 --> 00:40:58,686
And you stole my side dishes again!

677
00:40:58,770 --> 00:41:00,646
What do you know about love?

678
00:41:00,730 --> 00:41:04,233
Do you have any idea
what it feels like to love someone so much

679
00:41:04,317 --> 00:41:07,028
that giving all you have
still tears you apart inside?

680
00:41:11,908 --> 00:41:12,909
Damn it.

681
00:41:13,701 --> 00:41:16,662
It is like you are begging
to be torn from limb to limb.

682
00:41:16,746 --> 00:41:19,165
How dare you subject me
to your misdirected rage!

683
00:41:28,216 --> 00:41:31,219
-Min-a…
-Affairs of the heart are nothing special.

684
00:41:31,302 --> 00:41:33,012
He's acting like
some sad puppy in the rain.

685
00:41:33,096 --> 00:41:35,014
Min-a…

686
00:41:37,975 --> 00:41:39,310
What do you know about love?

687
00:41:39,393 --> 00:41:42,021
Then again, it'd be weird
if a Joseon woman knew what "romance" was.

688
00:41:42,105 --> 00:41:44,941
They all treat me like some fool
who does not understand.

689
00:41:51,028 --> 00:41:55,576
A LOVE STORY BETWEEN A MAN
AND A WOMAN, OR THE AFFAIR ITSELF

690
00:41:57,662 --> 00:41:59,872
As if that were anything
to write home about.

691
00:42:23,104 --> 00:42:27,233
Your Highness, this court lady has been
newly appointed to your quarters.

692
00:42:34,824 --> 00:42:36,325
Offer your greetings.

693
00:42:43,791 --> 00:42:46,085
I offer you my greetings, Your Highness.

694
00:42:47,879 --> 00:42:49,338
Lift your head.

695
00:42:51,215 --> 00:42:53,968
I despise having to repeat myself.

696
00:42:54,051 --> 00:42:55,303
Now.

697
00:43:07,523 --> 00:43:08,941
My lord, how…

698
00:43:09,775 --> 00:43:11,777
You lack basic discernment.

699
00:43:11,861 --> 00:43:14,155
This is why you get caught
in initiation rituals.

700
00:43:14,238 --> 00:43:15,823
Given your assignment to my quarters,

701
00:43:15,907 --> 00:43:18,993
it appears you have also fallen
out of favor with your superiors.

702
00:43:20,870 --> 00:43:22,246
That is not the case.

703
00:43:22,330 --> 00:43:25,541
My calligraphy is decent,
and I am skilled in classical Chinese.

704
00:43:26,250 --> 00:43:28,711
That was why I was assigned
to these quarters.

705
00:43:28,794 --> 00:43:31,172
This is why I say
you lack basic discernment.

706
00:43:35,009 --> 00:43:37,470
Have you not heard the rumors about me?

707
00:43:38,095 --> 00:43:39,096
Rumors?

708
00:43:39,180 --> 00:43:41,182
"The Ghost Prince with the damaged eye."

709
00:43:41,849 --> 00:43:43,684
"The blood-drinking Goblin Prince."

710
00:43:44,185 --> 00:43:46,020
That is what they whisper about me.

711
00:43:47,104 --> 00:43:48,356
What do you think?

712
00:43:48,439 --> 00:43:51,234
Are you scared now?

713
00:43:53,152 --> 00:43:55,154
With all due respect,

714
00:43:55,738 --> 00:43:57,698
I am not scared in the slightest.

715
00:43:58,658 --> 00:43:59,700
You are not?

716
00:43:59,784 --> 00:44:01,953
You saved me.

717
00:44:03,621 --> 00:44:04,664
I am not

718
00:44:05,706 --> 00:44:09,043
so ignorant as to fear my savior.

719
00:44:12,838 --> 00:44:14,006
How audacious.

720
00:44:14,090 --> 00:44:16,217
Speaking so freely in the palace

721
00:44:16,300 --> 00:44:18,177
is asking for an early death.

722
00:44:18,261 --> 00:44:19,887
If you wish to live a long life,

723
00:44:19,971 --> 00:44:21,931
you should first learn
to keep your mouth shut.

724
00:44:22,014 --> 00:44:24,058
I will take that to heart.

725
00:44:24,141 --> 00:44:25,393
Good.

726
00:44:28,229 --> 00:44:30,231
What is your name?

727
00:44:33,567 --> 00:44:36,487
Of course, my name is…

728
00:44:53,713 --> 00:44:55,172
Shin Seo-ri.

729
00:45:20,323 --> 00:45:21,365
Hey…

730
00:45:22,074 --> 00:45:25,036
you know how people cry in their sleep?

731
00:45:25,119 --> 00:45:27,288
How would a psychiatrist interpret that?

732
00:45:27,371 --> 00:45:28,831
It's usually one of two things.

733
00:45:28,914 --> 00:45:32,376
Either some bastard who stiffed you
on money showed up in your dreams,

734
00:45:32,460 --> 00:45:34,628
-or your first love did.
-"First love"?

735
00:45:34,712 --> 00:45:36,088
-You've lost your damn mind!
-Why?

736
00:45:36,172 --> 00:45:37,715
Did you dream about a woman you know?

737
00:45:37,798 --> 00:45:41,135
Anything else? Did she say
she was your first love from a past life?

738
00:45:42,345 --> 00:45:44,930
You call yourself a doctor
and talk about past lives?

739
00:45:45,014 --> 00:45:48,684
In psychiatry, dreams aren't
something you can ignore.

740
00:45:48,768 --> 00:45:50,853
Your subconscious knows you best.

741
00:45:50,936 --> 00:45:52,521
And? So what?

742
00:45:52,605 --> 00:45:55,024
When you dream something
out of the ordinary,

743
00:45:55,107 --> 00:45:56,942
isn't that life telling you to change?

744
00:45:57,026 --> 00:45:59,445
It's telling you to try jumping off

745
00:45:59,528 --> 00:46:01,739
that grinding hamster wheel
you call your life.

746
00:46:01,822 --> 00:46:04,617
Hey, suddenly jumping off
a moving object can get you killed.

747
00:46:04,700 --> 00:46:06,577
That would be a major accident.

748
00:46:06,660 --> 00:46:10,289
Then again, a meticulous planner like you
would never go off track.

749
00:46:10,373 --> 00:46:13,709
That is, unless, you've fallen in love.

750
00:46:15,086 --> 00:46:17,463
Our Se-gye has a woman in his life?

751
00:46:17,546 --> 00:46:18,881
A woman?

752
00:46:19,548 --> 00:46:22,093
As in a woman he is seeing?

753
00:46:22,176 --> 00:46:24,345
Yes, exactly. A girlfriend, a lover.

754
00:46:24,428 --> 00:46:27,556
As far as I'm aware, Mr. Cha
has neither a boyfriend nor a girlfriend.

755
00:46:27,640 --> 00:46:29,350
In fact, it'd be safe to say

756
00:46:29,433 --> 00:46:31,769
that he has not
a single soul in his orbit.

757
00:46:31,852 --> 00:46:34,438
No, I was told he definitely has a woman.

758
00:46:34,522 --> 00:46:37,566
Like a news anchor at a TV station.

759
00:46:37,650 --> 00:46:38,734
A news anchor?

760
00:46:38,818 --> 00:46:41,904
Or maybe a producer?

761
00:46:41,987 --> 00:46:43,197
A producer…

762
00:46:44,156 --> 00:46:45,783
There's no one.

763
00:46:47,159 --> 00:46:49,870
Mun-do isn't one to talk nonsense.

764
00:46:49,954 --> 00:46:51,539
President Choi Mun-do saw her?

765
00:46:52,164 --> 00:46:55,126
Mr. Cha's female acquaintance…
I mean, his girlfriend?

766
00:46:55,793 --> 00:46:58,170
I doubt it's true,
but I will look into it.

767
00:47:04,969 --> 00:47:06,887
This is not half bad.

768
00:47:06,971 --> 00:47:09,140
I used to enjoy eomandu quite often.

769
00:47:09,223 --> 00:47:10,391
The tops are burning.

770
00:47:10,474 --> 00:47:13,144
Seriously, why'd you follow me
to my part-time job?

771
00:47:13,227 --> 00:47:14,937
Stop eating and serve the customers.

772
00:47:15,646 --> 00:47:18,107
Don't you see the manager?
He won't stop staring at us.

773
00:47:18,190 --> 00:47:21,193
Fine, I hear you.
As if I have even eaten that much.

774
00:47:21,277 --> 00:47:22,736
You there!

775
00:47:22,820 --> 00:47:24,530
Come try some dumplings.

776
00:47:24,613 --> 00:47:26,782
Yes, delicious dumplings!
Come have a taste.

777
00:47:26,866 --> 00:47:29,243
They're pan-fried
to a perfect golden brown.

778
00:47:29,326 --> 00:47:30,870
Please come and try one.

779
00:47:30,953 --> 00:47:33,330
If you overcook them,
the filling dries out.

780
00:47:33,914 --> 00:47:35,332
It cannot be helped.

781
00:47:37,626 --> 00:47:40,379
Cook a new batch.
These are too dry to be served.

782
00:47:41,005 --> 00:47:42,506
He's coming! He's here!

783
00:47:42,590 --> 00:47:43,966
You two, hold on a second.

784
00:47:44,049 --> 00:47:45,468
I've been watching you.

785
00:47:45,551 --> 00:47:46,719
Are you aware

786
00:47:46,802 --> 00:47:49,597
that half of those sample dumplings
went into your mouth?

787
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:51,307
That I cannot say.

788
00:47:51,891 --> 00:47:53,392
I was not exactly keeping count.

789
00:47:53,476 --> 00:47:55,644
You're here to work, not eat.

790
00:47:55,728 --> 00:47:58,689
You can go over there and work
some overtime to make up for this.

791
00:47:58,772 --> 00:48:00,483
If you want to get paid, that is.

792
00:48:00,566 --> 00:48:03,569
My stomach just happens
to be full, so I shall.

793
00:48:06,322 --> 00:48:07,573
Wait…

794
00:48:11,702 --> 00:48:14,413
Sir, were you able
to retrieve your card without issue?

795
00:48:15,039 --> 00:48:16,916
Card? What card?

796
00:48:19,793 --> 00:48:22,254
-Well, you know…
-You could've just canceled it.

797
00:48:22,338 --> 00:48:25,508
But you went all that way to find it
in the middle of the night.

798
00:48:25,591 --> 00:48:28,135
Because it's my favorite card.

799
00:48:29,220 --> 00:48:30,137
Why?

800
00:48:30,221 --> 00:48:32,097
Oh, I was just curious.

801
00:48:32,181 --> 00:48:34,225
I see. So it was your favorite card.

802
00:48:36,519 --> 00:48:37,978
-Mr. Son.
-Sir.

803
00:48:38,062 --> 00:48:40,022
Do we have time
to stand around chit-chatting?

804
00:48:40,105 --> 00:48:42,608
I always tell you. Time is gold.

805
00:48:48,447 --> 00:48:50,908
Time is gold, but at night, of all times…

806
00:48:54,245 --> 00:48:55,955
No way. It can't be true.

807
00:48:56,038 --> 00:48:58,332
Mr. Cha has such impeccable taste.

808
00:48:58,415 --> 00:49:00,167
Unless he's lost his mind.

809
00:49:04,630 --> 00:49:05,673
Hello.

810
00:49:06,507 --> 00:49:07,925
These scoundrels.

811
00:49:13,889 --> 00:49:16,350
There is clearly
a cunning minx inside of her.

812
00:49:16,433 --> 00:49:18,686
Absolutely insufferable,
beyond all measure.

813
00:49:22,106 --> 00:49:24,233
-Are you a Yoon Ji-hyo fan too?
-A fan?

814
00:49:24,316 --> 00:49:26,986
You were staring so hard.
I thought you were a fan.

815
00:49:27,903 --> 00:49:30,197
Glaring at her like this makes me a fan?

816
00:49:30,281 --> 00:49:32,116
Silently rooting for them makes you a fan.

817
00:49:32,199 --> 00:49:35,035
You wish them well, worry about them,
and send them gifts.

818
00:49:35,119 --> 00:49:38,497
Celebrities make a living
thanks to their fans' love.

819
00:49:38,581 --> 00:49:41,166
Root for someone?
I am barely staying afloat as it is.

820
00:49:42,251 --> 00:49:44,295
You must be aware
that Biojei has staked everything

821
00:49:44,378 --> 00:49:46,213
on launching
our Dynaestie herbal cosmetics line,

822
00:49:46,297 --> 00:49:49,800
and just how crucial brand image is
for the company.

823
00:49:50,426 --> 00:49:53,762
Let's have one final in-depth meeting
to bring all our opinions together.

824
00:49:53,846 --> 00:49:57,099
The marketing team
strongly favors a new face.

825
00:49:57,182 --> 00:49:58,434
Since it's a new brand,

826
00:49:58,517 --> 00:50:01,353
we've determined
that a fresh image is crucial.

827
00:50:01,437 --> 00:50:02,521
You mean Shin Seo-ri?

828
00:50:02,605 --> 00:50:03,731
Absolutely not.

829
00:50:03,814 --> 00:50:05,774
We must not forget
the convertible bond risk.

830
00:50:05,858 --> 00:50:07,276
We must do all we can

831
00:50:07,359 --> 00:50:09,778
to ensure this launch is a success.

832
00:50:09,862 --> 00:50:12,615
I believe going with Yoon Ji-hyo
is the safer choice.

833
00:50:12,698 --> 00:50:15,367
I mean, was Yoon Ji-hyo
an A-list star from the start?

834
00:50:15,451 --> 00:50:19,163
In the entertainment world, one commercial
can make you an overnight sensation.

835
00:50:19,246 --> 00:50:21,624
Who's to say
that can't happen for Shin Seo-ri?

836
00:50:21,707 --> 00:50:23,125
It has to be Yoon Ji-hyo.

837
00:50:23,208 --> 00:50:25,544
New wine deserves a new bottle.
It has to be Shin Seo-ri.

838
00:50:25,628 --> 00:50:27,713
This is not the time
to take unnecessary risks.

839
00:50:27,796 --> 00:50:29,048
Let's just go with Yoon Ji-hyo.

840
00:50:29,131 --> 00:50:30,382
-Shin Seo-ri.
-Yoon Ji-hyo.

841
00:50:30,466 --> 00:50:31,759
-Shin Seo-ri.
-Yoon Ji-hyo.

842
00:50:31,842 --> 00:50:33,344
Shin Seo-ri is the way to go.

843
00:50:33,427 --> 00:50:36,263
Sir, the results
of the anonymous internal company vote

844
00:50:36,347 --> 00:50:37,640
just came in on the intranet.

845
00:50:37,723 --> 00:50:38,849
Please take a look.

846
00:50:45,606 --> 00:50:46,815
Your Majesty.

847
00:50:49,985 --> 00:50:52,237
-Your Majesty, how could you do this?
-My goodness.

848
00:50:52,321 --> 00:50:53,197
You wench!

849
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:55,574
How dare you seduce His Majesty?

850
00:50:55,658 --> 00:50:58,285
You are not a courtesan.
That is no way for a queen to act.

851
00:50:58,369 --> 00:51:00,079
-So undignified.
-When you were just a stray,

852
00:51:00,162 --> 00:51:01,830
-I took you in.
-Even I could do better.

853
00:51:01,914 --> 00:51:03,332
And this is how you repay me?

854
00:51:03,415 --> 00:51:04,833
You wench!

855
00:51:04,917 --> 00:51:08,087
When you were just a stray, I took you in.
And this is how you repay me?

856
00:51:08,170 --> 00:51:11,173
How dare you hold your head high
and threaten me?

857
00:51:11,256 --> 00:51:13,342
Guards, drag this wench away at once!

858
00:51:13,425 --> 00:51:15,928
How dare you hold your head high
and threaten me?

859
00:51:16,011 --> 00:51:17,137
Hear me!

860
00:51:17,221 --> 00:51:19,682
Drag that wench away
and crush her legs this instant!

861
00:51:19,765 --> 00:51:21,392
Oh my goodness. She's so good.

862
00:51:22,101 --> 00:51:24,353
You're way better than that Yoon Ji-hyo.

863
00:51:24,436 --> 00:51:25,896
Yes, absolutely.

864
00:51:25,979 --> 00:51:28,899
And you have such a pretty face.
You could be a celebrity.

865
00:51:34,863 --> 00:51:36,115
Do not just stand there!

866
00:51:36,198 --> 00:51:39,243
Drag that wench away at once
and give her a good thrashing!

867
00:51:42,329 --> 00:51:43,288
SHIN SEO-RI: 52%
YOON JI-HYO: 48%

868
00:51:43,372 --> 00:51:45,290
It's a close one.

869
00:51:45,374 --> 00:51:46,250
Even so,

870
00:51:46,333 --> 00:51:49,545
there can only be one winner.
That's the principle of majority rule.

871
00:51:56,051 --> 00:51:56,927
What?

872
00:52:01,265 --> 00:52:02,683
I mean, the staff has spoken.

873
00:52:02,766 --> 00:52:03,767
My hands are tied.

874
00:52:03,851 --> 00:52:06,103
A democratic CEO like myself

875
00:52:06,186 --> 00:52:08,689
can't just make a unilateral decision.

876
00:52:09,732 --> 00:52:10,941
Democracy is dead.

877
00:52:11,024 --> 00:52:13,235
Then it's decided. It'll be Shin Seo-ri.

878
00:52:13,318 --> 00:52:15,612
Get the contract ready and send it over.

879
00:52:15,696 --> 00:52:16,905
Yes, sir.

880
00:52:21,452 --> 00:52:22,828
SHIN SEO-RI

881
00:52:28,333 --> 00:52:30,419
But why was I abandoned?

882
00:52:31,003 --> 00:52:33,797
No matter how hard I think,
I can't figure it out.

883
00:52:33,881 --> 00:52:37,301
What did I do wrong?
No matter how hard I think…

884
00:52:37,384 --> 00:52:39,261
-Don't think like that.
-What do you know?

885
00:52:40,387 --> 00:52:42,306
Then why am I alone?

886
00:52:42,389 --> 00:52:44,600
Why am I the only one who's alone?

887
00:52:46,977 --> 00:52:49,521
They told me to wait.

888
00:52:51,273 --> 00:52:52,983
They said if I waited here…

889
00:52:53,066 --> 00:52:53,942
SONAGI

890
00:52:54,067 --> 00:52:56,570
…they'd be right back.

891
00:52:59,156 --> 00:53:01,867
They told me to wait here.

892
00:53:06,538 --> 00:53:07,873
What is wrong with me?

893
00:53:26,517 --> 00:53:27,392
That child…

894
00:53:27,476 --> 00:53:28,811
I remember her!

895
00:53:28,894 --> 00:53:31,063
She was so good at acting.

896
00:53:31,146 --> 00:53:32,481
You don't see her anymore.

897
00:53:32,564 --> 00:53:34,525
I know. A real child prodigy.

898
00:53:34,608 --> 00:53:36,652
She had her moment, then just disappeared.

899
00:53:36,735 --> 00:53:38,779
I saw her on an episode
of Screening Humanity.

900
00:53:38,862 --> 00:53:40,739
No parents. It was just her
and her grandma.

901
00:53:40,823 --> 00:53:42,616
What was her name again?

902
00:53:42,699 --> 00:53:44,117
Shin…

903
00:53:44,201 --> 00:53:46,370
-My goodness.
-Seo-ri.

904
00:53:46,453 --> 00:53:47,371
Shin Seo-ri.

905
00:53:48,205 --> 00:53:50,541
-That's it. Shin Seo-ri.
-Right! Shin Seo-ri.

906
00:53:50,624 --> 00:53:52,292
-It's her again.
-Wait a second.

907
00:53:52,376 --> 00:53:55,003
You're that young actress from before.

908
00:53:55,087 --> 00:53:57,339
You should really try being a celebrity.

909
00:53:57,422 --> 00:53:59,216
-My goodness.
-Your acting was great.

910
00:53:59,299 --> 00:54:01,718
-She's so pretty, isn't she?
-So pretty.

911
00:54:03,512 --> 00:54:04,471
Hey, Unit 203.

912
00:54:05,097 --> 00:54:06,682
What are you doing here?

913
00:54:06,765 --> 00:54:09,434
Why look at TVs
when you don't even have a home?

914
00:54:09,518 --> 00:54:11,603
They told me I should be a celebrity.

915
00:54:12,271 --> 00:54:14,606
Do they mean being on that TV?

916
00:54:16,108 --> 00:54:18,318
Well, yeah. Why do you ask?

917
00:54:19,152 --> 00:54:20,612
It is just fascinating.

918
00:54:22,573 --> 00:54:25,701
To make people cry and laugh
in an instant.

919
00:54:27,202 --> 00:54:31,415
The power to linger in one's memory
for so long, without even having met…

920
00:54:33,083 --> 00:54:34,710
I find that fascinating.

921
00:54:35,669 --> 00:54:37,546
As if that's anything to marvel at.

922
00:54:37,629 --> 00:54:39,172
Let's go get paid.

923
00:54:52,603 --> 00:54:53,812
The contract's a no-go?

924
00:54:53,896 --> 00:54:55,314
Doran Entertainment.

925
00:54:55,397 --> 00:54:58,442
Ms. Shin Seo-ri is
still under contract with them.

926
00:54:58,525 --> 00:55:00,068
It's contract renewal season right now.

927
00:55:00,152 --> 00:55:04,239
Normally, the star renews or moves on
before the campaign begins.

928
00:55:04,323 --> 00:55:06,158
-Okay.
-It seems the agency verbally informed her

929
00:55:06,241 --> 00:55:07,534
that they would not renew.

930
00:55:07,618 --> 00:55:10,495
But after hearing about the ad,
they're denying that ever happened.

931
00:55:10,579 --> 00:55:12,414
They had no intention of renewing,

932
00:55:12,497 --> 00:55:14,791
but if this ad deal goes through,
they may have to reassess,

933
00:55:14,875 --> 00:55:17,044
so they put a hold on canceling it.

934
00:55:17,127 --> 00:55:20,505
A small-time agency is putting us on hold?

935
00:55:22,799 --> 00:55:24,176
Set up a meeting.

936
00:55:24,885 --> 00:55:26,720
I want to see this CEO for myself.

937
00:55:29,806 --> 00:55:31,558
So what are you going to do?

938
00:55:31,642 --> 00:55:33,685
Of all people,

939
00:55:33,769 --> 00:55:35,687
I have to lose
to a nobody like Shin Seo-ri?

940
00:55:35,771 --> 00:55:38,148
That would be mortifying.
How could I ever show my face again?

941
00:55:38,231 --> 00:55:39,316
Just wait.

942
00:55:39,399 --> 00:55:40,859
Even if her contract's almost up,

943
00:55:40,943 --> 00:55:44,821
as long as we don't cooperate,
Shin Seo-ri can't sign anything.

944
00:55:44,905 --> 00:55:47,658
You know how unforgiving
the entertainment industry can be.

945
00:55:47,741 --> 00:55:49,034
I know.

946
00:55:49,117 --> 00:55:50,953
But what if some clueless agency
takes the bait?

947
00:55:51,036 --> 00:55:52,871
An ad campaign isn't
a winning lotto ticket.

948
00:55:52,955 --> 00:55:56,541
Who would sign a washed-up child actor
turned throwaway extra?

949
00:55:56,625 --> 00:55:58,794
But since they reached out,

950
00:55:58,877 --> 00:56:00,796
I'll at least go and hear them out.

951
00:56:00,879 --> 00:56:03,966
Then I'll go with you.
I need to hear for myself

952
00:56:04,049 --> 00:56:05,717
why they want to take on such a risk.

953
00:56:05,801 --> 00:56:09,012
SONAGI

954
00:56:31,493 --> 00:56:33,120
SLEEP IS FOR THE DEAD

955
00:56:33,245 --> 00:56:34,705
YOU WILL BECOME A STAR

956
00:56:34,830 --> 00:56:37,499
Do you wish for me
to carry on your dream?

957
00:56:38,375 --> 00:56:40,460
As payment for inhabiting your body,

958
00:56:40,544 --> 00:56:42,921
you want me to fulfill your dream
on your behalf?

959
00:56:43,005 --> 00:56:45,465
Is that why you stir my heart like this?

960
00:56:48,552 --> 00:56:50,762
Why do I keep…

961
00:57:01,940 --> 00:57:04,484
You're that young actress from before.

962
00:57:07,112 --> 00:57:09,573
You should really try being a celebrity.

963
00:57:09,656 --> 00:57:10,699
I need that.

964
00:57:10,782 --> 00:57:12,367
And in turn, you.

965
00:57:13,660 --> 00:57:14,703
Desperately, even.

966
00:57:24,254 --> 00:57:25,630
SPOKESPERSON CONTRACT: SHIN SEO-RI

967
00:57:25,714 --> 00:57:27,090
APPROVAL PENDING

968
00:57:38,310 --> 00:57:41,188
I shall give the contract
careful consideration.

969
00:57:41,772 --> 00:57:45,025
You even bribed me with Korean beef.
What choice do I have?

970
00:57:46,568 --> 00:57:49,112
Whatever. I'm sure she's used
to being rejected anyway.

971
00:57:49,196 --> 00:57:50,113
Why should I worry?

972
00:57:57,245 --> 00:57:58,121
Me, worry?

973
00:57:59,289 --> 00:58:01,208
Why would I worry about a woman like that?

974
00:58:31,905 --> 00:58:33,865
What the hell am I thinking right now?

975
00:58:38,745 --> 00:58:41,039
Listen, is a man named Cha Se-gye there?

976
00:58:44,084 --> 00:58:44,960
Shin Seo-ri?

977
00:58:45,043 --> 00:58:47,712
You recognized my voice so quickly.

978
00:58:47,796 --> 00:58:49,548
You must have been waiting for my call.

979
00:58:50,465 --> 00:58:51,341
Yes.

980
00:58:51,424 --> 00:58:53,301
This is the news
you have been dying to hear.

981
00:58:53,385 --> 00:58:54,636
I call bearing glad tidings.

982
00:58:54,719 --> 00:58:56,012
Glad tidings?

983
00:58:56,096 --> 00:58:58,348
In recognition
of your commendable sincerity,

984
00:58:58,849 --> 00:59:00,475
I have decided to grant you that contract.

985
00:59:00,559 --> 00:59:01,518
No, wait a minute.

986
00:59:01,601 --> 00:59:04,521
Look, a contract isn't
as simple as you think.

987
00:59:04,604 --> 00:59:05,689
Let us keep it simple.

988
00:59:05,772 --> 00:59:07,440
No need to overthink it.

989
00:59:07,524 --> 00:59:08,984
We shall just follow our gut.

990
00:59:09,067 --> 00:59:10,902
No, just let me finish talking.

991
00:59:10,986 --> 00:59:12,821
-Look, it's just that--
-Actually…

992
00:59:12,904 --> 00:59:15,782
I thought it would be best
to talk in person,

993
00:59:15,866 --> 00:59:17,325
so I am on my way.

994
00:59:18,451 --> 00:59:19,828
Where are you right now?

995
00:59:19,911 --> 00:59:20,829
I am right outside.

996
00:59:21,454 --> 00:59:23,665
I will be there soon.
Wait for me, Cha Se-gye.

997
00:59:23,748 --> 00:59:25,125
No, wait…

998
00:59:29,254 --> 00:59:31,548
I fought so hard for this chance at life.

999
00:59:32,382 --> 00:59:35,677
I cannot waste it being a doormat.

1000
00:59:36,303 --> 00:59:39,139
Since the master of this body urges me so,

1001
00:59:39,222 --> 00:59:40,223
I shall now try

1002
00:59:41,057 --> 00:59:42,893
forging my own destiny.

1003
00:59:56,740 --> 00:59:59,159
Hello, who are you here to see?

1004
00:59:59,242 --> 01:00:00,785
I have come seeking this man.

1005
01:00:01,661 --> 01:00:02,746
I was told to call him CEO.

1006
01:00:02,829 --> 01:00:03,705
The CEO?

1007
01:00:06,041 --> 01:00:09,211
It's you!
I guess you passed that audition?

1008
01:00:10,545 --> 01:00:13,882
He claimed he was in dire need of me
and wished to forge a contract.

1009
01:00:13,965 --> 01:00:15,258
Wow, that's great.

1010
01:00:15,342 --> 01:00:17,636
A hundred people a day come through here.

1011
01:00:17,719 --> 01:00:20,013
The fact that I remember
your face must mean

1012
01:00:20,096 --> 01:00:21,932
you've made a strong impression
on them as well.

1013
01:00:22,015 --> 01:00:23,308
Speaking of, I believe

1014
01:00:23,391 --> 01:00:26,144
I benefited from the good fortune
you wished upon me.

1015
01:00:26,228 --> 01:00:28,313
So I shall see to it that you are
greatly rewarded.

1016
01:00:28,396 --> 01:00:30,732
Rewards and punishments
must always be clear and just

1017
01:00:30,815 --> 01:00:32,692
to boost the morale of one's subjects.

1018
01:00:32,776 --> 01:00:36,071
You really sound like someone
from a historical drama.

1019
01:00:36,154 --> 01:00:38,114
Well then, best of luck to you once more.

1020
01:00:39,282 --> 01:00:41,243
Much obliged, as always.

1021
01:00:42,994 --> 01:00:44,371
Shin Seo-ri?

1022
01:00:56,007 --> 01:00:57,092
Shin Seo-ri.

1023
01:00:57,175 --> 01:00:58,677
Did you really think

1024
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:01,888
you could sign such a major contract
without my consent?

1025
01:01:01,972 --> 01:01:03,348
What reason would I have not to?

1026
01:01:04,266 --> 01:01:05,558
That dismissive tone again.

1027
01:01:05,642 --> 01:01:07,310
As for the termination notice,

1028
01:01:07,394 --> 01:01:09,145
that was merely verbal.

1029
01:01:09,229 --> 01:01:11,606
Your contract is still valid.

1030
01:01:11,690 --> 01:01:14,109
Pulling tricks behind the agency's back
without our consent?

1031
01:01:14,192 --> 01:01:16,653
Didn't you know that's all illegal?

1032
01:01:16,736 --> 01:01:19,781
I am not in a position to leisurely worry
about taking the proper channels,

1033
01:01:19,864 --> 01:01:21,199
so I had no other choice.

1034
01:01:21,283 --> 01:01:23,660
Are you giving me riddles right now?

1035
01:01:23,743 --> 01:01:24,995
Yes.

1036
01:01:25,620 --> 01:01:28,081
I suppose it is this wench's turn
to step in now.

1037
01:01:28,164 --> 01:01:30,125
Watch your mouth. Don't you know

1038
01:01:30,208 --> 01:01:32,168
a single scandal can ruin you?

1039
01:01:32,252 --> 01:01:34,045
Especially with a contract on the line.

1040
01:01:34,129 --> 01:01:36,840
You're not a complete nobody.
Shouldn't you be more careful?

1041
01:01:36,923 --> 01:01:40,510
Judging by the way you behave,
I would not say that is wholly true.

1042
01:01:41,136 --> 01:01:43,096
I shall take your advice to heart.

1043
01:01:43,179 --> 01:01:45,181
If you are done talking,
I should be on my way.

1044
01:01:45,265 --> 01:01:46,266
I have a prior engagement.

1045
01:01:49,269 --> 01:01:50,979
Where do you think you're going?

1046
01:01:51,855 --> 01:01:53,106
What the…

1047
01:01:53,815 --> 01:01:55,317
This old fox is surprisingly strong.

1048
01:01:55,400 --> 01:01:57,694
Let go of my hand
before I snap your arm clean in two.

1049
01:01:57,777 --> 01:01:59,738
What? "Snap it in two"?

1050
01:01:59,821 --> 01:02:01,990
You should be grateful that I took you in

1051
01:02:02,073 --> 01:02:04,242
when you were starving and wasting away.

1052
01:02:04,868 --> 01:02:07,537
So you do not wish to be snapped in two?

1053
01:02:08,163 --> 01:02:09,039
In that case…

1054
01:02:12,250 --> 01:02:13,793
-Stop it!
-Oh my God!

1055
01:02:13,877 --> 01:02:14,878
What in the world?

1056
01:02:14,961 --> 01:02:15,879
How could you…

1057
01:02:15,962 --> 01:02:17,130
Damn it.

1058
01:02:22,594 --> 01:02:24,304
Well, look at you.

1059
01:02:26,431 --> 01:02:28,141
I have come to pay my respects.

1060
01:02:28,224 --> 01:02:29,267
You wench!

1061
01:02:29,351 --> 01:02:30,560
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM
EPISODE 14

1062
01:02:37,817 --> 01:02:39,194
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM
EPISODE 36

1063
01:02:39,319 --> 01:02:40,278
Damn it.

1064
01:02:44,991 --> 01:02:47,077
Oh my, is no one around…

1065
01:02:48,536 --> 01:02:52,165
Gosh, what is wrong with them?

1066
01:02:53,708 --> 01:02:55,460
Oh man, this is insane.

1067
01:02:55,543 --> 01:02:58,588
Yeah. These royal court dramas
are all about the slapping.

1068
01:03:00,673 --> 01:03:02,384
Has a woman come looking for me?

1069
01:03:08,098 --> 01:03:09,682
Experience makes all the difference.

1070
01:03:09,766 --> 01:03:11,142
Are you tired already?

1071
01:03:11,810 --> 01:03:15,313
Then again, you tried your best
with those flimsy wrists of yours.

1072
01:03:15,397 --> 01:03:19,067
Everyone mistakes me
for some delicate flower,

1073
01:03:19,150 --> 01:03:21,611
but do you have any idea
how I got to where I am?

1074
01:03:21,694 --> 01:03:24,739
Girls like you who don't know their place?

1075
01:03:24,823 --> 01:03:25,907
I walked all over them.

1076
01:03:25,990 --> 01:03:28,618
Looks like this wench
has not been slapped enough.

1077
01:03:28,701 --> 01:03:30,203
Still running that mouth like that.

1078
01:03:30,286 --> 01:03:31,287
"Wench"?

1079
01:03:32,372 --> 01:03:34,707
-Why you--
-That's enough from both of you.

1080
01:03:39,045 --> 01:03:41,464
Oh my goodness. Ji-hyo!

1081
01:03:41,548 --> 01:03:43,842
Hey, pull yourself together.

1082
01:03:43,925 --> 01:03:45,260
Come on, get up.

1083
01:03:45,343 --> 01:03:47,220
Here. Sit here.

1084
01:03:57,564 --> 01:03:59,482
Is this any way to behave
in someone else's office?

1085
01:03:59,566 --> 01:04:01,568
What are you going to do about this?

1086
01:04:01,651 --> 01:04:04,737
Our Ji-hyo has a shoot tomorrow.
What are you going to do about her face?

1087
01:04:04,821 --> 01:04:07,073
Did you not hear me say that's enough?

1088
01:04:07,157 --> 01:04:09,451
I'm someone who despises
repeating himself.

1089
01:04:10,118 --> 01:04:12,829
Who are you to tell me to stop?

1090
01:04:13,955 --> 01:04:15,373
-Who am I?
-Yeah.

1091
01:04:15,457 --> 01:04:18,668
Who are you to butt in
when you don't know what's going on?

1092
01:04:18,751 --> 01:04:21,212
She is right. This is my issue to handle.

1093
01:04:21,296 --> 01:04:22,422
Stay out of it, Cha Se-gye.

1094
01:04:25,341 --> 01:04:26,342
"Cha Se-gye"?

1095
01:04:26,426 --> 01:04:29,471
As in the CEO of Biojei?

1096
01:04:29,554 --> 01:04:31,389
Allow me to formally introduce myself.

1097
01:04:33,725 --> 01:04:35,226
Let me tell you who I am.

1098
01:04:46,279 --> 01:04:48,531
"Biojei Entertainment"?

1099
01:04:48,615 --> 01:04:51,784
I'm from Shin Seo-ri's new agency.

1100
01:04:52,410 --> 01:04:55,330
Cha Se-gye,
the CEO of Biojei Entertainment.

1101
01:04:56,456 --> 01:04:57,624
What? Hold on.

1102
01:04:59,959 --> 01:05:02,504
Then I have a right to step in.

1103
01:05:02,587 --> 01:05:03,546
Don't I?

1104
01:05:04,422 --> 01:05:07,467
What is with that arrogant smile?

1105
01:05:09,719 --> 01:05:11,679
I look forward to working with you,

1106
01:05:12,096 --> 01:05:12,972
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

1107
01:05:17,060 --> 01:05:19,896
For an enemy general
to extend his hand during wartime

1108
01:05:19,979 --> 01:05:22,148
means he does not want to fight.

1109
01:05:24,984 --> 01:05:28,196
Then is this a peace offering?

1110
01:05:28,279 --> 01:05:30,156
Don't leave me hanging.

1111
01:05:31,366 --> 01:05:32,742
You have to seal the deal.

1112
01:05:33,493 --> 01:05:34,410
"Seal the deal"?

1113
01:05:34,494 --> 01:05:37,205
We seal it with a handshake,
like a stamp on your palm.

1114
01:05:38,289 --> 01:05:39,374
Like this.

1115
01:05:44,879 --> 01:05:46,005
Deal…

1116
01:05:48,466 --> 01:05:49,634
sealed.

1117
01:05:59,644 --> 01:06:03,189
This handsome lunatic keeps smiling at me.

1118
01:06:05,483 --> 01:06:07,360
It is giving me the chills.

1119
01:06:34,345 --> 01:06:37,098
Your Highness, the court maid
you asked about

1120
01:06:37,181 --> 01:06:39,726
has safely entered
Grand Prince Cheongheon's quarters.

1121
01:06:39,809 --> 01:06:42,604
Yes, it appears so.

1122
01:06:43,771 --> 01:06:45,106
Well done.

1123
01:06:51,946 --> 01:06:55,116
But may I ask why you brought her here?

1124
01:06:55,199 --> 01:06:58,494
She has no backing
and is not one of your people.

1125
01:07:01,039 --> 01:07:03,041
She will become a useful snare

1126
01:07:03,124 --> 01:07:05,251
for my younger brother one day.

1127
01:07:05,335 --> 01:07:07,587
So watch her closely.

1128
01:07:08,129 --> 01:07:09,297
Yes, Your Highness.

1129
01:07:21,809 --> 01:07:24,812
A no-name actress and Cha Se-gye.

1130
01:07:26,189 --> 01:07:27,482
What an amusing pair.

1131
01:07:27,565 --> 01:07:30,693
Putting them together
could be quite something.

1132
01:07:30,777 --> 01:07:32,028
Shin Seo-ri.

1133
01:07:32,111 --> 01:07:33,946
Let's make that woman the variable.

1134
01:07:36,115 --> 01:07:38,284
That Shin Seo-ri is such a pain.

1135
01:07:49,003 --> 01:07:52,507
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1136
01:08:25,623 --> 01:08:28,167
Ms. Shin, you come this way.
Here. Towards me.

1137
01:08:28,251 --> 01:08:29,961
Of course. He must be my fan.

1138
01:08:30,044 --> 01:08:31,838
No. Of course not.

1139
01:08:31,921 --> 01:08:34,632
I intend to give this handwritten letter
to my fan as a reverse tribute.

1140
01:08:34,716 --> 01:08:35,717
This woman is in love with me.

1141
01:08:35,842 --> 01:08:37,468
Before we enter into this contract,
let's set one ground rule first.

1142
01:08:37,552 --> 01:08:39,178
From now on, let's be sure to keep

1143
01:08:39,262 --> 01:08:40,388
our professional
and personal lives separate.

1144
01:08:40,471 --> 01:08:43,224
You came because you were worried
and missed me, right?

1145
01:08:43,307 --> 01:08:45,893
The contractee owes
a duty of care to the contractor.

1146
01:08:45,977 --> 01:08:49,397
She misunderstood after I took pity
on her and helped her out a few times.

1147
01:08:49,480 --> 01:08:50,940
You pity me?

1148
01:08:56,153 --> 01:08:58,153
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
